!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

signify /ˈsɪɡnɪˌfaɪ/

(signifying,signified,signifies) 

1. V-T If an event, a sign, or a symbol signifies something, it is a sign of that thing or represents that thing. 表示; 意味着 

例： These were not the only changes that signified the end of boyhood. 这些不是表示男孩时代已结束的惟一变化。 

2. V-T If you signify something, you make a sign or gesture in order to communicate a particular meaning. (用符号或手势) 表达 

例： Two jurors signified their dissent. 两个陪审员表达了他们的异议。

